Source: pg-pathcheck
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), perl
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/danolivo/pg_pathcheck

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-pathcheck
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-pathcheck
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Planner Path diagnostics preload module for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 pg_pathcheck is a PostgreSQL debug aid that validates planner Path trees
 for freed or garbage memory. It installs a shared library module that must
 be loaded through shared_preload_libraries.
